From: gcc-for-Windows98 build pipeline
Subject: [PATCH] skip NT security descriptor in process_init() on Win98

GNU make 4.4.1's Windows pipe-setup (sub_proc.c::process_init) builds a
SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES struct with an empty-DACL SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR so the
inheritable stdin/stdout/stderr pipes it CreatePipe()'s grant
nonrestricted access — necessary on NT, where passing NULL would attach
the calling process's default security descriptor (restricted).

InitializeSecurityDescriptor is exported by Win98 SE's ADVAPI32.DLL but
it's a stub: it always sets the LastError and returns FALSE on the Win9x
kernel. The static PE import binds cleanly, the call fails at runtime,
and process_init() bails before any pipe is created — make then fails to
launch any subprocess (the gating condition is "make can spawn any
recipe at all"). The PE verifier's behavioral denylist rejects the
import too.

On Win9x there's no security model at all: lpSecurityDescriptor is
ignored by CreatePipe / CreateProcess / every other inheritable-handle
producer. So we drop the InitializeSecurityDescriptor call AND pass NULL
for lpSecurityDescriptor on Win98 — the NT-only concern from the
upstream comment (default-SD attached on NULL) literally doesn't apply.

Activated by -D_WIN98_PORT (matches the gating convention in the
busybox-w32 patch series). Without that define the upstream code path
is preserved verbatim.

--- a/src/w32/subproc/sub_proc.c
+++ b/src/w32/subproc/sub_proc.c
@@ -401,15 +401,27 @@
            Instead we use a security descriptor with no DACL.  This
            allows nonrestricted access to the associated objects. */

+#ifndef _WIN98_PORT
         if (!InitializeSecurityDescriptor((PSECURITY_DESCRIPTOR)(&sd),
                                           SECURITY_DESCRIPTOR_REVISION)) {
                 pproc->last_err = GetLastError();
                 pproc->lerrno = E_SCALL;
                 return((HANDLE)pproc);
         }
+#endif

         inherit.nLength = sizeof(inherit);
+#ifdef _WIN98_PORT
+        /* Win9x ignores lpSecurityDescriptor (no security model). The NT
+         * comment above does not apply: there is no "default security
+         * descriptor of the calling process" on Win98 — NULL is fine.
+         * Avoids a static import of advapi32!InitializeSecurityDescriptor,
+         * which is a stub-only export on Win98 SE. */
+        (void)sd;
+        inherit.lpSecurityDescriptor = NULL;
+#else
         inherit.lpSecurityDescriptor = (PSECURITY_DESCRIPTOR)(&sd);
+#endif
         inherit.bInheritHandle = TRUE;

         /* By convention, parent gets pipe[0], and child gets pipe[1].
